tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a new calming, sleep-themed color
  palette, redesigned key sections like the intro and main form, and polished
  various UI components to create a more professional and engaging user
  experience.
overview: The user wanted to enhance the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was functional but lacked aesthetic polish.
  I began by analyzing the existing design, identifying areas such as the
  generic color palette, plain layouts, and basic form elements as key
  improvement opportunities. The approach involved a comprehensive aesthetic
  overhaul, starting with a new calming, sleep-themed color palette. I then
  redesigned the main questionnaire form, introducing subtle background
  elements, an improved progress indicator, and a star pattern overlay on card
  headers. The intro section was transformed with a hero element and feature
  cards, while individual form components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and
  sliders received significant styling updates for better visual feedback and
  interaction. Section groupings were refined into more appealing cards, and the
  report section was updated for consistency with the new theme. All changes
  compiled successfully, moving the app from a generic template look to a more
  professional and engaging interface tailored for a sleep health application.
